glosses: To itch for trouble, to ask for trouble.

etymology: From Ottoman Turkish قاشینمق (ḳaşınmaḳ, “reflexive; to scratch one's self, to itch”), from Ottoman Turkish قاشیمق (ḳaşımaḳ, “transitive; to scratch with the nails”), from Proto-Turkic *kaĺı- (to scrape, to scratch), morphologically kaşı- + -n- + -mak.
